36 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
37 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
38 Article – Agriculture

HOUSE BILL 972 3
1 SUBTITLE 22. MARYLAND FAIR AND AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION PROMISE FUND.
2 10–2201.
3 IN THIS SUBTITLE, “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND FAIR AND AGRICULTURAL
4 EDUCATION PROMISE FUND.
5 10–2202.
6 (A) THERE IS A MARYLAND FAIR AND AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION
7 PROMISE FUND.
8 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE GRANTS THAT ADVANCE
9 AGRICULTURAL FAIRS AND EDUCATION IN THE STATE.
10 (C) THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
11 (D) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
12 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
13 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY,
14 AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
15 (E) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
16 (1) REVENUE DISTRIBUTED TO THE FUND UNDER § 9–120(B)(1)(XV)
17 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE;
18 (2) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
19 (3) (2) INTEREST EARNINGS; AND
20 (4) (3) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED
21 FOR THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
22 (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY:
23 (1) TO PROVIDE ANNUAL GRANTS IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–2203
24 OF THIS SUBTITLE; AND
25 (2) FOR ADMINISTRATIVE EXPENSES OF THE COMPTROLLER IN
26 CARRYING OUT THIS SUBTITLE.

4 HOUSE BILL 972
1 (G) (1) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND
2 IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
3 (2) ANY INTEREST EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE CREDITED TO
4 THE FUND.
5 (H) EXPENDITURES FROM THE FUND MAY BE MADE ONLY IN ACCORDANCE
6 WITH THE STATE BUDGET.
7 (I) FOR EACH FISCAL YEAR, THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE
8 ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF $200,000 TO THE FUND.
9 10–2203.
10 EACH YEAR, THE COMPTROLLER SHALL PAY FROM THE FUND AN ANNUAL
11 GRANT OF:
12 (1) $825,000 TO THE MARYLAND AGRICULTURAL FAIR BOARD TO
13 PROMOTE AND ENHANCE STATE AND COUNTY AGRICULTURAL FAIRS AND EXHIBITS;
14 (2) (1) $75,000 $100,000 TO THE MARYLAND AGRICULTURAL
15 EDUCATION FOUNDATION, INC., TO PROMOTE AND ENHANCE STATEWIDE
16 AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION; AND
17 (3) $550,000 TO THE MARYLAND STATE FAIR AND AGRICULTURAL
18 SOCIETY, INC., TO:
19 (I) PROMOTE AND ENHANCE THE STATE AGRICULTURAL FAIR;
20 AND
21 (II) MAINTAIN AND DEVELOP YOUTH AGRICULTURAL
22 PROGRAMS, WITH SUBSTANTIAL FUNDING PROVIDED TO ORGANIZATIONS,
23 INCLUDING 4–H CLUBS AND THE MARYLAND FFA ASSOCIATION, FOR THE
24 PROVISION OF RECOGNITION AND AWARDS; AND
25 (4) (2) $50,000 $100,000 TO THE MARYLAND FFA ASSOCIATION
26 FOR AGRICULTURAL EDUCATION AND CAREER DEVELOPMENT.
